(this["webpackJsonpzume-pwa"]=this["webpackJsonpzume-pwa"]||[]).push([[5],{452:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"t":"Session 5","assets":[{"type":"audio","key":"prayer-walking"},{"type":"video","key":"person-of-peace"}],"sections":[{"t":"LOOKING BACK","parts":[{"t":"CHECK-IN","d":["Before getting started, take some time to check-in.","At the end of the last session, everyone in your group was challenged in two ways:",["You were asked to share your 3-Minute Testimony with at least one person on your List of 100.","You were encouraged to train someone else with the 3-Minute Testimony tool."],"Take a few moments to see how your group did this week."]},{"t":"PRAY","d":"Pray and thank God for the results and invite His Holy Spirit to lead your time together."},{"t":"OVERVIEW","d":"In this session, you\u2019ll learn how Prayer Walking is a powerful way to prepare a neighborhood for Jesus, and you\'ll learn a simple but powerful pattern for prayer that will help you meet and make new disciples along the way."}]},{"t":"Prayer Walking and How To Do It","d":"It\u2019s a simple way to obey God\u2019s command to pray for others. And it\'s just what it sounds like \u2014 praying to God while walking around!","duration":15,"parts":[{"type":"read","d":[{"t":"Prayer Walking","d":"Prayer Walking is a simple way to obey God\u2019s command to pray for others. And it\'s just what it sounds like \u2013 praying to God while walking around!"}]},{"type":"listen","payload":{"audio":"prayer-walking"}}]},{"t":"A Person of Peace and How To Find One","d":"Learn who a person of peace might be and how to know when you\'ve found one.","duration":15,"parts":[{"type":"watch","d":"Disciple-making can be rapidly advanced by finding a person of peace, even in a place where followers of Jesus are few and far between. How do you know when you have found a person of peace and what do you when you find them?","payload":{"video":"person-of-peace"}},{"type":"discuss","questions":["Can someone who has a \\"bad reputation\\" (like the Samaritan woman or the demon-possessed man in the Gadarenes) really be a Person of Peace? Why or why not?","What is a community or segment of society near you that seems to have little (or no) Kingdom presence? How could a Person of Peace (someone who is OPEN, HOSPITABLE, KNOWS OTHERS and SHARES) accelerate the spread of the Gospel in that community?"]}]},{"t":"Practice the B.L.E.S.S. Prayer (15min)","d":"Practice a simple mnemonic to remind you of ways to pray for others.","duration":15,"info":"Break into groups of two or three and practice the B.L.E.S.S. Prayer.","parts":[{"d":["Here are five ways you can pray for people you meet during your Prayer Walk:","As you walk and pray, be alert for opportunities and listen for promptings by God\u2019s Spirit to pray for individuals and groups you meet along the way.","You can say, \u201cWe\u2019re praying for this community, is there anything in particular we can pray for you about?\u201d Or say, \u201cI\u2019m praying for this area. Do you know anything in particular we should pray for?\u201d After listening to their response you can ask about their own needs. If they share, pray for them right away. If the Lord leads, you may pray about other needs as well.","Use the word B.L.E.S.S. to help you remember 5 different ways you can pray:",["Body [health]","Labor [job and finances]","Emotional [morale]","Social [relationships]","Spiritual [knowing and loving God more]"],"In most cases, people are grateful you care enough to pray.","If the person is not a Christian, your prayer may open the door to a spiritual conversation and an opportunity to share your story and God\u2019s story. You can invite them to be a part of a Bible study or even host one in their home.","If the person is a Christian you can invite them to join your Prayer Walk or train them how they can Prayer Walk and use simple steps like praying for areas of influence or the B.L.E.S.S. Prayer to grow God\u2019s family even more."]}]},{"t":"Prayer Walking (60-90min)","d":["The session ends with a prayer walking activity.","Read through the Obey, Share, and Pray sections, below, before you head out!"],"duration":90,"info":["Break into groups of two or three and go out into the community to practice Prayer Walking.","Choosing a location can be as simple as walking outside from where you are now, or you could plan to go to a specific destination.","Go as God leads, and plan on spending 60-90 minutes on this activity."]},{"t":"LOOKING FORWARD","parts":[{"t":"OBEY","d":"Spend time this week practicing Prayer Walking by going out alone or with a small group at least once."},{"t":"SHARE","d":"Spend time asking God who He might want you to share the Prayer Walking tool with before your group meets again. Share this person\u2019s name with the group before you go."},{"t":"PRAY","d":"Before you go out on your Prayer Walking activity, be sure to pray with your group to end your time together. Thank God that He loves the lost, the last and the least \u2013 including us! Ask Him to prepare your heart and the heart of those you\'ll meet during your walk to be open to His work."},{"t":"#ZumeProject","d":"Take a picture of something you see on your prayer walk and post it on social media. "}]}]}')}}]);
